Custom compiled hipBLASLt DLL for AMD Radeon RX 9070 XT on Windows.
The stock DLL shipped with the AMD AI Bundle (Ollama 0.13.5) does not recognise
gfx1201. It silently falls back to CPU inference with no error or warning.
This build fixes that.

Hardware Tested

GPU: AMD Radeon RX 9070 XT (gfx1201, RDNA4, 16 GB VRAM)
OS: Windows 11
ROCm: 7.x (amdhip64_7.dll)
Ollama: 0.13.5 (AMD AI Bundle)


What This Fixes
Stock DLL behaviour on gfx1201:

GPU not recognised
Silent fallback to CPU
All model layers loaded into system RAM
GPU completely idle during inference

With this DLL:

gfx1201 detected natively (no HSA_OVERRIDE needed)
All 33 layers offloaded to GPU on Llama 3 8B Q4_0
Flash Attention enabled automatically
138 t/s eval rate on Llama 3 8B Q4_0


Installation

Locate your Ollama ROCm directory:
%LOCALAPPDATA%\AMD\AI_Bundle\Ollama\lib\ollama\rocm\
Back up the existing DLLs:
rename the dlls or move them to a separate folder hipblaslt.dll, rocblas.dll ,amdhip64_6.dll, amd_comgr_2.dll 
Copy and place the dlls from the zip here
Don't touch the ggml-hip.dll in the root rocm\ directory.
Make a copy of the rocblas\library first and save it as rocblas\OLDlibrary 
Then add the files from zip to the rocblas\library and any overwrite file that is present.
Restart Ollama
Run ollama serve and confirm you see:
library=ROCm | compute=gfx1201
in the startup log


Verification
Run a quick test:
powershellollama run llama3 "Calculate 2^20" --verbose
You should see eval rate around 135-140 t/s with all 33 layers on GPU.
If you still see GPULayers: [] or device=CPU in the logs, the DLL is
not in the right directory.

Notes

No HSA_OVERRIDE_GFX_VERSION environment variable required
First inference after a cold start will be slower due to HIP JIT kernel
compilation - this is normal behaviour, not a bug. Subsequent runs are full speed.
Vulkan path also works without this DLL - but ROCm gives marginally better
prompt eval throughput


Build Info
Compiled targeting gfx1201 (RDNA4) on ROCm 7.x.
[Add your build flags / cmake options here if you want to share them]

Tested With

Meta Llama 3 8B Instruct, Q4_0 GGUF
Ollama 0.13.5

Other models should work - not tested yet.



Issues
If it doesn't work, open an issue with your ollama serve log output.
The key lines to look for are the inference compute and load_tensors sections.
